records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded. Statements made as to sentencing. Additional Statements made by Julie C.

As to COUNT 1-
Court ordered defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction concurrent to COUNT 2; credit for 1 day time served.

As to COUNT 2-
Court ordered defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction concurrent to COUNT 1; credit for 1 day time served.

Court STAYED the sentence on COUNTS 1 & 2 and placed defendant on probation for 3 YEARS with the following conditions:
1) Sex offender evaluation and comply with recommended treatment/counseling;
2) No unsupervised contact with anyone under the age of 16 years;
3) Electronic devices must be turned over to agent for inspection upon demand;
4) Defendant may not maintain any social media accounts;
5) Maintain absolute sobriety;
6) Random urine screens;
7) Provide any prescriptions to agent PRIOR to filling them;
8) Obtain HSED and maintain at least 20 hours of employment per week. Once the HSED is completed, defendant is to continue with vocational training or maintain employment of at least 30 hours per week.
9) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges on COUNT 1. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
10) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge on COUNT 1;

Court WAIVED costs, fees, surcharges, and DNA surcharge on COUNT 2 as it is part of a continuous event;

Court will defer a ruling on sex offender registration until a probation review date. 

Department of Corrections to submit a report to the Court for the probation review hearing. 

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
Probation Review Hearing scheduled for May 6, 2016 at 8:30 a.m.
